ime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:29:    \"description\" : \"Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.11.5/reachability-metadata.json:669:      \"glob\": \"META-INF/services/io.jsonwebtoken.io.Deserializer\"\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:12:    \"description\": \"jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:32:    \"description\": \"jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.\",\nmetadata/com.squareup.okio/okio/1.17.2/reachability-metadata.json:5:      \"serializable\": true\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:478:      \"glob\": \"META-INF/services/io.jsonwebtoken.io.Deserializer\"\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.12.7/reachability-metadata.json:609:      \"glob\": \"META-INF/services/io.jsonwebtoken.io.Deserializer\"\nmetadata/org.hibernate.validator/hibernate-validator/7.0.4.Final/reachability-metadata.json:325:      \"type\": \"java.io.ObjectInputStream\"\nmetadata/org.jboss/jandex/2.4.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json:19:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.11.5/reachability-metadata.json:567:      \"glob\": \"META-INF/services/io.jsonwebtoken.io.Deserializer\"\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:12:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based serializer and deserializer so JWT headers and claims can be read and written using JSON-Java. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android applications and supports simple object-to-JSON marshaling instead of POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:28:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based serializer and deserializer so JWT claims and headers can be read and written using JSON-Java. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android applications and supports simple object-to-JSON marshaling rather than POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:48:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementation for processing JWT content at runtime. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android use cases and supports simple claim marshaling without POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.zookeeper/zookeeper-jute/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache ZooKeeper Jute provides ZooKeeper's binary serialization and code-generation layer. It defines and generates the record classes used to marshal and unmarshal ZooKeeper protocol messages and related data structures.\",\nmetadata/org.objenesis/objenesis/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Objenesis is a Java library for instantiating objects without invoking their constructors. It is commonly used by serialization, proxying, and mocking frameworks that need to create objects beyond standard reflection.\",\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.5.0/reachability-metadata.json:2848:        \"typeReached\": \"com.hazelcast.internal.serialization.impl.SerializerHookLoader\"\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.5.0/reachability-metadata.json:2860:        \"typeReached\": \"com.hazelcast.internal.serialization.impl.SerializerHookLoader\"\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.5.0/reachability-metadata.json:2872:        \"typeReached\": \"com.hazelcast.internal.serialization.impl.SerializerHookLoader\"\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/ha