l serialize even if they’re null, which gives me pause about how the class descriptor is handled for null fields.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting class registration**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the registration process and suspect it’s limited to actual serialized classes. The class descriptor contains field type names while the class has field descriptors. I need to register the LogEvent, which should cover everything. The Priority is an actual object, and strings seem to be built-in. Maybe there's no need for the ContextMap if it's null, but I wonder if the LogEvent constructor might set it up. I’ll need to inspect the bytecode to be sure.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PPlU5KQmsw50COaQzLrZ77d0|fc_0884aea41be5cac90169ef7f7ff7248196b3108d45ab088418", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath /home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/velocity/velocity-dep/1.4/b1df5193d3dd66a310b32828c547cd9e163b98df/velocity-dep-1.4.jar -c -p org.apache.log.LogEvent | sed -n '1,220p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 612, "output": 686, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27410, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777303409541, "responseId": "resp_0884aea41be5cac90169ef7f71fdfc8196b6b1a8f2c0488bf8"}}
